0: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## References\n74: \n75: - Spec: `changes/AR-034/spec.md`\n76: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md`\n77: - Proposal: `changes/AR-034/proposal.md`\n78: - Tasks: `changes/AR-034/tasks.md`\n79: - [TO BE FILLED: Add relevant references]\n\n(End of file - total 79 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 вҖ” CI/CD GitHub Actions Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-034 вҖ” CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) |\n| Module | `.github` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Add design overview]\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/design.md","time":{"start":1775889160722,"end":1775889160733}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889160737,"sessionID":"ses_284c266ecffec55s5eapOZAOMv","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3e19f4001t10aAW2td7fIgm","messageID":"msg_d7b3e053e0018ADT2b33EV3BDf","sessionID":"ses_284c266ecffec55s5eapOZAOMv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8eb20fd2e29f4e56bc1b7b23a61e309f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 вҖ” CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n2: \n3: ## жҰӮиҝ°\n4: \n5: | еұһжҖ§ | еҖј |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-034 |\n8: | Module | .github |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (зӣ®зҡ„)\n15: \n16: Establish a comprehensive CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions for the AgentCube project, automating build verification, code quality checks, testing, and release workflows. This proposal implements 12 workflows covering:\n17: \n18: 1. **Build Verification**: Docker image builds on pull requests\n19: 2. **Code Quality**: Go lint, Python lint (Ruff), spelling checks (codespell), copyright headers\n20: 3. **Testing**: Unit tests with coverage, E2E tests on Kind, Python SDK tests\n21: 4. **Code Generation**: Validation of generated artifacts\n22: 5. **Release**: Multi-architecture image publication to GitHub Container Registry\n23: 6. **Workflow Management**: Auto-approval for trusted contributors\n24: \n25: **Workflow Summary**:\n26: \n27: | Workflow | Purpose |\n28: |----------|---------|\n29: | `main.yml` | Docker build verification on PRs |\n30: | `e2e.yml` | End-to-end tests on Kind cluster |\n31: | `lint.yml` | Go linting (golangci-lint) |\n32: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK unit tests |\n33: | `python-lint.yml` | Python linting (Ruff) |\n34: | `test-coverage.yml` | Go test coverage reporting |\n35: | `codegen-check.yml` | Generated code validation |\n36: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright header consistency |\n37: | `codespell.yml` | Spelling verification |\n38: | `build-push-release.yml` | Image publication on main/tags |\n39: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify plugin packaging and publishing |\n40: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Auto-approve trusted contributor runs |\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## 2. Scope (иҢғеӣҙ)\n45: \n46: ### 2.1 In Scope\n47: \n48: | Deliverable | Description |\n49: |-------------|-------------|\n50: | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Pull request Docker build verification |\n51: | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | Kind-based E2E testing workflow |\n52: | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go linting with path filtering |\n53: | `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK pytest execution |\n54: | `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Ruff-based Python linting |\n55: | `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Go test coverage with Codecov integration |\n56: | `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Generated code drift detection |\n57: | `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright header validation |\n58: | `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Repository-wide spelling check |\n59: | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Multi-arch image push to ghcr.io |\n60: | `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify plugin release automation |\n61: | `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | First-time contributor workflow approval |\n62: \n63: ### 2.2 Workflow Trigger Matrix\n64: \n65: | Workflow | Triggers | Branches | Path Filters |\n66: |----------|----------|----------|--------------|\n67: | `main.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | None |\n68: | `e2e.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | None |\n69: | `lint.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml` |\n70: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | вҖ” | `sdk-python/**` |\n71: | `python-lint.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py` |\n72: | `test-coverage.yml` | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | вҖ” | All minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` |\n73: | `codegen-check.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` |\n74: | `copyright-check.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | All minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` |\n75: | `codespell.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | None |\n76: | `build-push-release.yml` | `push` | `main`, tags `v*.*.*` | None |\n77: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | `push` tags | `dify-plugin/v*` | None |\n78: | `workflows-approve.yml` | `pull_request_target` | `main`, `release-**` | None |\n79: \n80: ### 2.3 Out of Scope\n81: \n82: | Item | Reason |\n83: |------|--------|\n84: | GitHub self-hosted runners | Using GitHub-hosted runners (ubuntu-latest) |\n85: | Custom CI infrastructure | Standard GitHub Actions suffices |\n86: | Third-party CI systems (Jenkins, GitLab CI) | GitHub-native solution preferred |\n87: | Deployment workflows | Deployment handled by Helm in clusters |\n88: | Security scanning (SAST/DAST) | Future AR for security tooling |\n89: | Performance benchmarks | Not in initial CI scope |\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 3. Impact Analysis (еҪұе“ҚеҲҶжһҗ)\n94: \n95: ### 3.1 ж–°еўһж–Үд»¶\n96: \n97: | File | Description |\n98: |------|-------------|\n99: | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Docker build workflow |\n100: | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | E2E test workflow |\n101: | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go lint workflow |\n102: | `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK test workflow |\n103: | `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Python lint workflow |\n104: | `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Coverage workflow |\n105: | `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Codegen check workflow |\n106: | `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright check workflow |\n107: | `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Spelling check workflow |\n108: | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Release build workflow |\n109: | `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify plugin publish workflow |\n110: | `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | Workflow approval workflow |\n111: \n112: ### 3.2 дҝ®ж”№ж–Үд»¶\n113: \n114: | File | Change |\n115: |------|--------|\n116: | None | All workflows are new additions |\n117: \n118: ### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n119: \n120: | Dependency | Purpose |\n121: |------------|---------|\n122: | `actions/checkout@v4` | Repository checkout |\n123: | `actions/setup-go@v5` | Go toolchain installation |\n124: | `actions/setup-python@v5` | Python toolchain installation |\n125: | `docker/setup-buildx-action@v3` | Docker Buildx setup |\n126: | `docker/login-action@v3` | Container registry authentication |\n127: | `docker/build-push-action@v5` | Multi-arch image builds |\n128: | `helm/kind-action@v1` | Kind cluster setup |\n129: | `dorny/paths-filter@v3` | Path-based workflow filtering |\n130: | `codecov/codecov-action@v4` | Coverage upload |\n131: | `github-script` | GitHub API operations |\n132: \n133: ### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n134: \n135: | Consumer | Usage |\n136: |----------|-------|\n137: | Pull Request authors | Automatic validation on PRs |\n138: | Maintainers | Quality gate enforcement |\n139: | Release process | Automated image publishing on tags |\n140: | Dify plugin users | Plugin availability via dify-plugins repo |\n141: | First-time contributors | Streamlined workflow approval |\n142: \n143: ### 3.5 Makefile Targets Required\n144: \n145: | Target | Workflow | Description |\n146: |--------|----------|-------------|\n147: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `e2e.yml` | Build workload manager image |\n148: | `docker-build-router` | `e2e.yml` | Build router image |\n149: | `docker-build-picod` | `e2e.yml` | Build picod image |\n150: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image |\n151: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n152: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n153: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run E2E test script |\n154: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | Cleanup E2E resources |\n155: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | Run golangci-lint |\n156: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code |\n157: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (еӨҮйҖүж–№жЎҲ)\n162: \n163: ### Alternative 1: Single Monolithic Workflow\n164: \n165: **Approach**: Combine all CI steps into a single workflow file.\n166: \n167: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n168: |--------|------------|\n169: | Pros | Simpler structure, single file to maintain |\n170: | Cons | No parallel execution, longer feedback loop, all-or-nothing failure, no selective triggering |\n171: \n172: **Decision**: Rejected. Multiple workflows enable parallel execution, faster feedback, and path-based selective triggering. Critical checks (lint, build) complete faster than longer checks (E2E).\n173: \n174: ### Alternative 2: GitLab CI / Jenkins\n175: \n176: **Approach**: Use alternative CI/CD platforms.\n177: \n178: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n179: |--------|------------|\n180: | Pros | Potential for self-hosted infrastructure, different feature sets |\n181: | Cons | GitHub is the canonical repository; external CI adds complexity; no native GitHub integration |\n182: \n183: **Decision**: Rejected. GitHub Actions provides native integration with the repository, requires no external infrastructure, and uses the same platform as the code hosting.\n184: \n185: ### Alternative 3: Composite Actions for Reused Steps\n186: \n187: **Approach**: Extract common steps (setup, checkout) into composite actions.\n188: \n189: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n190: |--------|------------|\n191: | Pros | DRY principle, centralized maintenance |\n192: | Cons | Additional complexity for minimal code; current duplication is acceptable for clarity |\n193: \n194: **Decision**: Rejected for initial implementation. May reconsider if step duplication becomes unmanageable. Current workflow count (12) is manageable.\n195: \n196: ### Alternative 4: Dependabot for Action Versioning\n197: \n198: **Approach**: Use Dependabot to auto-update action versions.\n199: \n200: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n201: |--------|------------|\n202: | Pros | Automatic security updates, version tracking |\n203: | Cons | Adds dependency management overhead; pinning to major versions is sufficient |\n204: \n205: **Decision**: Rejected for now. Pinning to major versions (v3, v4, v5) provides stability while allowing minor updates. Can add Dependabot configuration in a future AR.\n206: \n207: ### Alternative 5: Reusable Workflows for Coverage\n208: \n209: **Approach**: Extract test-coverage.yml as a reusable workflow callable from other workflows.\n210: \n211: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n212: |--------|------------|\n213: | Pros | Reusability across multiple calling workflows |\n214: | Cons | Only test-coverage.yml uses `workflow_call`; no other callers exist |\n215: \n216: **Decision**: Partially adopted. `test-coverage.yml` already uses `workflow_call` for future reusability, but this is not the primary pattern for other workflows.\n217: \n218: ### Alternative 6: Self-Hosted Runners for E2E\n219: \n220: **Approach**: Use self-hosted runners with pre-configured Kind clusters for faster E2E.\n221: \n222: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n223: |--------|------------|\n224: | Pros | Faster E2E execution, persistent Kind clusters |\n225: | Cons | Infrastructure overhead, security considerations, maintenance burden |\n226: \n227: **Decision**: Rejected. GitHub-hosted runners provide consistent, isolated environments with zero maintenance overhead. E2E execution time is acceptable (~10-15 minutes).\n228: \n229: ### Alternative 7: Merge Queue with Branch Protection\n230: \n231: **Approach**: Use GitHub merge queues instead of PR-based checks.\n232: \n233: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n234: |--------|------------|\n235: | Pros | Ensures linear history, serialized merges |\n236: | Cons | Additional configuration, not needed for current team size |\n237: \n238: **Decision**: Rejected for now. `merge_group` trigger is supported in `test-coverage.yml` and `python-sdk-tests.yml` for future merge queue adoption. Current PR-based workflow is sufficient.\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ## 5. Risks\n243: \n244: | Risk | Mitigation |\n245: |------|------------|\n246: | Action version deprecation | Pin to major versions; monitor deprecation notices |\n247: | Rate limiting on GitHub Actions | Path filtering reduces unnecessary runs; workflow approval for first-time contributors |\n248: | E2E flakiness | Kind cluster isolation; artifact collection on failure; cleanup in `always()` block |\n249: | Registry credentials exposure | Use `GITHUB_TOKEN` (built-in) for ghcr.io; no long-lived secrets |\n250: | Coverage report size | Only cover `./pkg/...`; upload as artifact for large reports |\n251: | False positives in codespell | Temporary file removal for known false positives; ignore list for common issues |\n252: | Buildx cache growth | Use GitHub Actions cache; prune old caches periodically |\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n257: \n258: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/` directory structure\n259: - [ ] Implement `main.yml` with Docker build verification\n260: - [ ] Implement `e2e.yml` with Kind cluster and test execution\n261: - [ ] Implement `lint.yml` with path filtering for Go files\n262: - [ ] Implement `python-sdk-tests.yml` with pytest execution\n263: - [ ] Implement `python-lint.yml` with Ruff configuration\n264: - [ ] Implement `test-coverage.yml` with Codecov integration\n265: - [ ] Implement `codegen-check.yml` with `make gen-check`\n266: - [ ] Implement `copyright-check.yml` with `make gen-copyright`\n267: - [ ] Implement `codespell.yml` with ignore list configuration\n268: - [ ] Implement `build-push-release.yml` with multi-arch builds\n269: - [ ] Implement `dify-plugin-publish.yml` with cross-repo PR creation\n270: - [ ] Implement `workflows-approve.yml` with contributor check\n271: - [ ] Add required secrets to repository settings (`CODECOV_TOKEN` optional, `PLUGIN_ACTION` for dify)\n272: - [ ] Configure branch protection rules requiring status checks\n273: - [ ] Test each workflow with sample PRs\n274: \n275: ---\n276: \n277: ## 7. References\n278: \n279: - GitHub Actions Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/actions\n280: - Docker Buildx Documentation: https://docs.docker.com/buildx/working-with-buildx/\n281: - Kind Documentation: https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/\n282: - golangci-lint: https://golangci-lint.run/\n283: - Ruff: https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/\n284: - Codecov: https://docs.codecov.com/\n285: - ci-cd/spec.md вҖ” CI/CD requirements specification\n286: - ci-cd/design.md вҖ” CI/CD design documentation\n287: - test/e2e/run_e2e.sh вҖ” E2E test execution script\n288: - Makefile вҖ” Build and test targets\n\n(End of file - total 288 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 вҖ” CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n## жҰӮиҝ°\n\n| еұһжҖ§ | еҖј |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-034 |\n| Module | .github |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (зӣ®зҡ„)\n\nEstablish a comprehensive CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions for the AgentCube project, automating build verification, code quality checks, testing, and release workflows. This proposal implements 12 workflows covering:\n\n1. **Build Verification**: Docker image builds on pull requests\n2. **Code Quality**: Go lint, Python lint (Ruff), spelling checks (codespell), copyright headers\n3. **Testing**: Unit tests with coverage, E2E tests on Kind, Python SDK tests","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775889160725,"end":1775889160735}}}}
